race.comment: Wide open. DAYTONA DIVA (6) was a maiden winner on debut then put away. Returned with a strong run behind the unbeaten Mazzini in what will be a good form race. Can only be fitter and expected to go close again. SNOWDONIA (3) resumed over 1220m and hit the line strongly to finish a close-up fourth. Fitter for that and looks hard to hold out here with any lucky from the wide gate. COAL RIVER (1) was having first run for the new yard here fresh and led throughout, lifting to hold on by a nose. Surely fitter again and off a low draw will take catching. THE TRINE (2) is an honest type who finally got off the mark latest with a strong on pace win at Launceston. Has a good draw and will push forward again.
